---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Lynn Baxter">
  <main class="container about">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <img class="portrait" src="/assets/portrait-sketching.jpg" alt="Lynn Baxter sketching on a tablet from the corner of a grey couch" width="220" height="293" />
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="lead">I build tools for families and test them on my own.</p>
      <p>
        I&rsquo;m Lynn, a product designer, former facilities manager, and systems thinker living in Albany, California with my loud, complicated, thoroughly blended family. I studied biology before spending nearly a decade running offices and buildings for San Francisco startups, first at Slack and later at Blend. Those careers turned out to have more in common than I expected. Every complex system develops failure points. Most problems aren&rsquo;t surprises, they&rsquo;re signals that nobody had time to notice.
      </p>
      <p>
        The hardest systems work I&rsquo;ve ever done wasn&rsquo;t in an office. It was at home.
      </p>
      <p>
        Caregivers make decisions with incomplete information all day long. Every grandparent, babysitter, teacher, coach, and family member needs a different version of the same truth. Most families manage it with screenshots, text threads, sticky notes, memory, and luck.
      </p>
      <p>
        I think we can do better.
      </p>
      <p>
        So I build the tools I wish existed, starting with problems my own family actually has. I prototype them, live with them, watch where they fail, iterate, and write honestly about what I learn. Most of the work you&rsquo;ll find here grew out of real mornings, real logistics, and real mistakes.
      </p>
      <p>
        Along the way I&rsquo;ve retrained in UX design through BloomTech, worked as a freelance product designer, narrated audiobooks, written children&rsquo;s stories and fiction, and studied early childhood education at Berkeley City College. Those experiences may seem unrelated to some, but to me it&rsquo;s always been the same: understanding how people think, learn, communicate, and care for one another so it&rsquo;s possible for us to build a community together.
      </p>
      <p>
        I&rsquo;m endlessly interested in systems, language, education, and the quiet infrastructure that helps families function.
      </p>
      <p>
        I have an unreasonable amount of enthusiasm for systems, edge cases, and problems that require creative solutions. If that&rsquo;s your kind of work too, <a class="reach" href="mailto:lynnmariebee@gmail.com">I&rsquo;d love to hear what you&rsquo;re building</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    .about { padding-block: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 3rem) clamp(3rem, 8vw, 4rem); max-width: 680px; }
    .portrait { width: 220px; height: auto; border-radius: var(--radius); margin: 1rem 0 2rem; }
    .prose .lead {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 1.2rem + 1.9vw, 2.1rem);
      font-weight: 500;
      line-height: 1.15;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    }
    .prose p { font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.35vw, 1.15rem); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.3rem; max-width: 60ch; color: var(--color-ink); }
    .prose em { font-style: italic; color: var(--color-clay); }
    .reach { color: var(--color-clay); text-decoration-thickness: 1px; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
    .reach:hover { text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }
  </style>
</Base>
